An Act strengthening GPS tampering Laws.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 209A is hereby further amended in section 7 by inserting after the word “system”
2 at the end of the eighth paragraph the following new paragraph:-
3 “The removal or destroying of said global positioning satellite tracking device without
4 judicial approval or without a showing of necessity to prevent greater harm shall constitute a
5 felony with a mandatory minimum sentence of 2 years in a state prison.”
